have clear instructions, please choose some options for your","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.clarificationStartMessage2":"document.","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.clarificationStartMessage3":"presentation.","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.clarificationStyleLabel":"Select a style for your content","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.clarificationSubmitButtonText":"Let's go","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.clarificationThemeLabel":"Select a theme","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.clarificationThemeThumbnailAltText":"Theme thumbnail","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.clarificationToggleOptionsAriaLabel":"Clarification form","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.excelClarificationTitle":"Workbook Options","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.powerPointClarificationTitle":"Presentation Options","scc-cowork-agent.coworkAgent.wordClarificationTitle":"Document Options","scc-cowork-agent.coworkHomePage.addReferencesOrNewPage":"Add References or a new page to get started","scc-cowork-agent.coworkHomePage.inputBoxPlaceholder":"Ask Copilot to research, draft, act, or create from your Notebook","scc-cowork-agent.coworkHomePage.inputBoxPlaceholderNotebookWorkdataWeb":"Ask Copilot to research, draft, act, or create from your Notebook, Work data, Web","scc-cowork-agent.coworkHomePage.taskHistoryTitle":"Chats","scc-cowork-agent.coworkHomePage.title":"Let's knock something off your list","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.createProgressTracker.command":"Analyse all references in this Notebook scoped to [project] and create a progress tracker.\n\nStep 1: Strictly scan only the existing Notebook references.\nStep 2: Extract all action items, open threads, and commitments (explicit or implied).\nStep 3: Consolidate and organise items by owner (explicit or inferred) and priority.\nStep 4: Suggest due dates only when contextual signals exist (timelines, urgency, dependencies); otherwise set to TBD.\nStep 5: Add all items to a new Tracker page in this Notebook with fields: item; owner; priority - due date or TBD; source reference; confidence level","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.createProgressTracker.title":"Create a progress tracker","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.curateFaq.command":"Analyse all references and pages in this Notebook and create an FAQ page.\n\nStep 1: From Notebook references and pages only, identify recurring themes, key topics, and commonly addressed concepts.\nStep 2: For each theme, generate an FAQ‑style set of relevant questions based only on explicitly stated information in the Notebook content, that the user might have.\nStep 3: Draft clear, concise answers for each question using only evidence‑backed content from the Notebook references or pages.\nStep 4: Group questions and answers by theme into a structured FAQ format. Ensure all answers are factually grounded in the Notebook content. Do not infer or generalise beyond explicitly supported information.\nStep 5: For each answer, include a citation or link to the supporting Notebook reference.\nStep 6: Create a comprehensive FAQ page in this Notebook containing: Theme; Question; Answer; Source reference","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.curateFaq.title":"Curate an FAQ page","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.executeFromFile.command":"Draft and send a stakeholder update email on [project] to [recipients] using references already in this Notebook only.\n\nStep 1: From Notebook references only, extract evidence‑backed information for: current status; recent milestones; upcoming milestones; key risks (and mitigations if explicitly stated); decisions needed / asks (if any).\nStep 2: Resolve overlapping or conflicting information using explicit evidence; prefer the most recent or most authoritative reference. If any element is not explicitly supported, mark it as TBD. Do not guess.\nStep 3: Draft the email with this structure: Subject: [project name] - Status update | Milestone | Asks (if any). Do not infer status, risks, or decisions without explicit supporting evidence.\nStep 4: Send the email to the specified recipients.","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.executeFromFile.title":"Send an update","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.expandNotebookKnowledge.command":'Find and add recent work data related to [project or topic] to this Notebook.\n\nStep 1: Search the user\'s work graph for recent files, meetings, emails, and other relevant artefacts from the last 30 days that reference the above specified project or topic, excluding anything already present in this Notebook.\nStep 2: Identify which items are relevant enough to be added as references. Relevance criteria should include: explicit project/topic mentions, contextual associations (e.g., shared attendees, shared file structures, repeated themes), attachments or linked resources connected to the topic.\nStep 3: Add each qualifying item to the References section of this Notebook.\nStep 4: Show a summary in the chat with: count and list of new references added ("what was added"), and a short explanation for each addition ("why it was added").',"scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.expandNotebookKnowledge.title":"Add references to Notebook","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.generateStatusDeck.command":"Analyse all references strictly in this Notebook related to [project] and generate an 8–12 slide PowerPoint status deck.\n\nStep 1: Extract relevant facts, top metrics, key decisions, risks, and planned actions, next steps from the Notebook references only.\nStep 2: Normalise and reconcile overlapping or conflicting information across references.\nStep 3: Populate slides covering: cover, goals, progress vs. plan, top metrics, key decisions, risks and mitigations, and next steps.\nStep 4: For progress, risks, and next steps, infer missing details (e.g., owners, timelines) only when supported by explicit contextual evidence; otherwise mark them as TBD and clearly distinguish inferred content from stated information.","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.generateStatusDeck.title":"Generate a status deck","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.prepareForMeeting.command":"Prepare a one‑page briefing for my upcoming meeting: [use '/' to select the meeting or describe it here].\n\nStep 1: Retrieve the calendar invite details and identify any linked documents or meeting artefacts.\nStep 2: Collect relevant context from the last 14 days across emails, Teams chats, notes, and transcripts that mention the meeting topic, attendees, or stated agenda.\nStep 3: Extract and organise content into these sections: Context (what & why now); Attendees (roles & likely priorities, based on invite context) — don't make up roles or due dates if there is no supporting evidence; Recent signals (top 3–5 threads/docs/notes); Open threads & risks; My prior commitments (with status); 2–3 recommended talking points (with a clear ask and rationale). All data should be factually correct.\nStep 4: Save the briefing to this Notebook and add citations/links for each supporting artefact.","scc-cowork-agent.coworkPromptSuggestions.prepareForMeeting.title":"Prepare for a meeting","scc-cowork-agent.coworkScopePicker.scopeNotebook":"This Notebook","scc-cowork-agent.coworkScopePicker.scopeNotebookWorkdataWeb":"This Notebook, Work data, Web","scc-cowork-agent.coworkScopePicker.teachingPopover.body":"Expand this chat beyond your notebook\nto include work data and the web.","scc-cowork-agent.coworkScopePicker.teachingPopover.primaryButton":"Got it","scc-cowork-agent.coworkScopePicker.teachingPopover.title":"Change your chat scope","scc-cowork-agent.coworkTaskHistory.seeMore":"See more","scc-cowork-agent.m365chat.coworkDetailsPanel.closeLabel":"Close details panel","scc-cowork-agent.m365chat.coworkDetailsPanel.inputsEmptyDescription":"Reference files will appear here","scc-cowork-agent.m365chat.coworkDetailsPanel.inputsEmptyTitle":"No context yet","scc-cowork-agent.m365chat.coworkDetailsPanel.outputsEmptyDescription":"Generated files will appear here","s