cise. Confirm assumptions and ask for missing details before finalising anything.\n\nREQUIRED INPUTS (ask if not provided; confirm values before sending):\n- Candidate Name\n- Role / Job Title\n- Department\n- Salary (amount + currency + cadence)\n- Start Date\n- Offer Expiry Date\n- Hiring Manager\n- Recruiter (optional)\n\nSCENARIO: [User describes what's happening in 1–2 sentences.]\n\nACTIONS (select or recommend the best fit based on the scenario):\n1. Draft Offer Letter — Formal letter covering role, compensation, benefits overview, start date, offer expiry, contingencies, and acceptance instructions.\n2. Schedule Offer Review — 30-min calendar invite + pre-meeting email. Agenda: role overview, comp walkthrough, benefits summary, Q&A. Invite recruiter and hiring manager.\n3. Send Reminder — Friendly nudge when the offer is nearing expiry or response is overdue. Include expiry date and next-step options.\n4. Negotiate Terms — Respond to a counter-offer with reasoning and proposed next steps. Flag approval needs and guardrails. Include revised terms when approved.\n5. Escalate — Status summary to hiring manager with urgency level, risks, decision needed, and recommended action.\n\nOUTPUT (always include both):\n1. Communication — Draft email (Outlook-ready) and/or offer letter (Word-ready), or calendar invite with title, attendees, agenda, and proposed time.\n2. Internal Notes — Log: date, action taken, context, inputs used, decisions/approvals, and next steps (for the HR file).\n\nExport all generated documents and artefacts to a new folder on my OneDrive.","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.legalContractReviewLabel":"Contract Review","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.legalContractReviewPrompt":'You are **Senior Legal Advisor** representing []. You are acting solely in [] interest throughout this review.\n\nReview the uploaded contract and identify **material risks only** — focus on clauses that could create significant legal, financial, or operational exposure for []. For each risk, provide:\n- A plain-English explanation of what the clause means and why it matters\n- The specific legal risk it poses to []\n- A suggested edit or redline\n\nThen ask: "What would you like to do next?"\n\nFollow-up options:\n1. Draft a redline of the full contract with tracked changes\n2. Draft a counter-proposal on [clause] and generate a revised document\n3. Draft an escalation email to legal leadership with a risk summary\n4. Schedule a meeting to walk through the flagged terms\n5. Draft a clarification email to the counterparty on [clause]',"scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.legalRegulatoryRiskMonitoringLabel":"Regulatory Risk Monitoring","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.legalRegulatoryRiskMonitoringPrompt":'I want to proactively identify legal and regulatory risks related to [my domain] while aligning with company objectives.\n\nReview my Outlook emails and Teams chats from this week and provide a structured summary of **material legal and regulatory developments only** — focus on issues with real compliance or business impact, not exhaustive coverage. For each finding, **cite the specific email, message, or document** it came from.\n\nStructure the output as:\n- **TLDR**: 2-3 sentence executive summary of the most important risks\n- **Key Developments**: Bullet list of material issues with source citations\n- **Compliance Impacts**: What action or decision is required, and by when\n- **Recommended Actions**: Specific next steps (not generic escalation)\n\nThen ask: "What would you like to do next?"\n\nFollow-up options:\n1. Draft an email to my manager summarising the top risks (I will review before sending)\n2. Create a Word document "Weekly Legal & Regulatory Risk Summary"\n3. Create a PowerPoint "Weekly Legal Risk Briefing" (Key Developments, Risks, Compliance Impacts, Actions)\n4. Set up a recurring weekly calendar invite "Legal Risk Review" (I will review before sending)',"scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingBrandingLabel":"Branding","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingBrandingPrompt":'I want to review [content name or campaign suite] against brand voice, tone, and messaging standards and deliver a complete, actionable brand compliance package ready for stakeholder approval and routing. Review any brand guide, prior content, compliance inputs, or multi-source brand materials I\'ve provided. Build a brand review using five dimensions: voice and tone, terminology and messaging alignment, style guide compliance, legal and compliance flags, and design asset brand adherence: anchored to the Brand Voice Config Block; if no brand guide exists, scaffold one before beginning the review. For campaign-scope requests, compile the Campaign Review Package and apply the full compliance artefact set. Scale depth to match scope: a single pre-publication check produces a ranked findings report; a full campaign pass produces the complete compliance and approval artefact set. Flag anything critical that\'s missing and suggest assumptions for confirmation.\n\nAfter generating the brand review:\n- Create a Word document titled "[Content Name] Brand Review Report" with severity-ranked findings, before/after revisions, and compliance flags.\n- Create an Excel spreadsheet titled "[Content Name] Content Feedback Tracker" recording intake log, review cycle status, and approval routing.\n- Create a Word document titled "[Content Name] Approval Routing Summary" mapping the approver chain by asset type and finding severity.\n- For campaign scope, also create a Campaign Review Package, QA Checklist, and Approval Form.\n- Draft an approval request email routing flagged items to reviewers; ask my approval before sending.',"scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingCampaignPlanningLabel":"Campaign planning","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingCampaignPlanningPrompt":'I want to build a [campaign name] campaign plan aligned to [primary goal] and ready to present to stakeholders. Review any prior campaigns, benchmark KPIs, messaging frameworks, or materials I\'ve provided. Build a campaign plan covering five stages: Objective, Audience, Message, Channel, and Measure: including the SMART goal, audience profile, message hierarchy with proof points, justified channel selection, budget allocation, and campaign-type-specific KPIs. Scale the depth to match the campaign: a blog post needs a 1-page brief; a product launch needs a full strategy document. Flag anything critical that\'s missing and suggest assumptions for confirmation.\n\nAfter generating the campaign plan:\n- Create a Microsoft Word document titled "[Campaign Name] Campaign Plan" with the full five-stage plan.\n- Create a PowerPoint presentation titled "[Campaign Name] Kickoff Brief" summarising: Objectives, Audience, Key Messages, Channel Plan, Timeline, KPIs.\n- Draft an email to the campaign stakeholder team with a TLDR and key decisions for their review; ask my approval before sending.\n- Create a calendar invite titled "[Campaign Name] Kickoff Meeting"; ask my approval before sending.',"scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingCompetitiveAnalysisLabel":"Competitive Analysis and Intelligence","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingCompetitiveAnalysisPrompt":'I want to build a competitive intelligence brief on [competitor set or market] aligned to [strategy, campaign, or sales use case] and ready for team distribution and response planning. Review any prior competitive research, competitor configs, market intelligence, and win/loss data I\'ve provided. Build a competitive brief covering six areas: research scope configuration, competitor profiling with value proposition and narrative arc analysis, messaging comparison matrix, content gap analysis, opportunities and threats, and response ideation with adversarial vulnerability assessment. Scale depth to match the trigger: a delta update covers what changed in the last 90 days; a full brief includes all sections plus the Competitor Analysis Deck and Market Insights Report. Flag anything critical that\'s missing and suggest assumptions for confirmation.\n\nAfter generating the competitive brief:\n- Create a Word document titled "[Competitor/Market] Competitive Brief" covering the 7-section structured report.\n- Create a PowerPoint presentation titled "[Competitor/Market] Competitor Analysis Deck" summarising competitive findings for stakeholder distribution.\n- Draft a stakeholder email summarising key competitive threats and recommended responses; ask my approval before sending.',"scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingCompetitiveLandscapeLabel":"Competitive Landscape","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingCompetitiveLandscapePrompt":"We need the competitive landscape report with positioning matrix for [insert competitor]. Search across my work data and web for the competitor annual reports, new announcements and current positioning against them. Also check any conversations on competitor benchmarks and comparisons. Build a presentation with a positioning matrix comparing each competitor on key dimensions like [x], [y], [z]. After generating the deck, draft an email to the team sharing it and schedule a 45-minute review meeting with [persons] for later this week.","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingContentPlanningLabel":"Content Planning","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingContentPlanningPrompt":'I want to plan and draft [content type or campaign asset suite] aligned to [audience and campaign objective] and ready for stakeholder review and publication. Review any brand guide, campaign brief, source document, or prior content I\'ve provided. Build a content plan covering all applicable sections: audience alignment, channel strategy, content structure, messaging hierarchy, SEO guidance, and content calendar: and produce near-final draft copy for each requested content type. Flag anything critical that\'s missing and suggest assumptions for confirmation.\n\nAfter generating the content plan and drafts:\n- Create a Word document titled "[Campaign/Topic] Content Plan" covering the full structured plan.\n- Create a Word document for each confirmed content type titled "[Content Type] Draft: [Campaign/Topic]" containing near-final copy ready for editorial review.\n- Build a Content Calendar in Excel titled "[Campaign/Topic] Content Calendar" with the publication schedule, owners, and channel assignments.\n- Draft an approval request email for stakeholder sign-off on the plan and drafts; ask my approval before sending.',"scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingPerformanceReportingLabel":"Performance Reporting","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.marketingPerformanceReportingPrompt":'I want to build a [campaign, channel, or cross-channel] marketing performance report for [period] aligned to [objective or stakeholder audience] and ready for leadership review and sales team handoff. Review any performance data, analytics exports, campaign strategy documents, and KPI frameworks I\'ve provided. Confirm the report type, time period, and data source before building. Triage data quality and attribute each metric to a named source before analysis begins. Build a performance report covering all 8 sections: executive summary, 6-column key metrics dashboard, trend analysis, What Worked / What Needs Improvement, insights, recommendations in a 2x2 matrix, attribution model, and Next Period Focus. Scale depth to match cadence: a weekly standup produces a summary format; a QBR produces the full report with attribution modelling and sales handoff artefacts.\n\nAfter generating the performance report:\n- Create a Word document titled "[Campaign/Period] Marketing Performance Report."\n- Create a Word document titled "[Campaign/Period] Campaign Performance Summary Report" for cross-team distribution.\n- Create a PowerPoint titled "[Campaign/Period] Campaign Insights Deck" for the sales alignment meeting.\n- Draft a stakeholder distribution email with key findings; ask my approval before sending.',"scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.nextSlideLabel":"Next","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.pitchNewProjectLabel":"Pitch a new project","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.pitchNewProjectPrompt":"Help me build a compelling case for a new project I want to pitch to leadership. <Describe the idea: problem, target users, and why it matters. Provide context.>\n\nFirst, research the landscape:\n- Internal context – search my emails, Teams messages, and documents for prior discussions, decisions, or related work\n- Problem space – search the web for trends, data, and pain points\n- Competitive analysis – identify the top 3–5 competitors, what they do, strengths, weaknesses, and opportunity gaps\n\nThen produce two deliverables:\n- Detailed report covering: internal landscape, market context, competitive analysis, proposed solution, effort/risks, and full references (all sources cited)\n- Executive PowerPoint: problem, market context, competitive landscape, proposed solution, why us, effort/risks, and recommended next steps. One point per slide, no walls of text","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.planWeekAheadLabel":"Plan my week ahead","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.planWeekAheadPrompt":"Help me plan my week.\n\nFirst, look back:\n- Review last week's commitments\n- Pull transcripts from recent meetings (including recurring ones) for context\n\nThen analyse this week's meetings. For key ones, enrich with:\n- Emails, chats, and related meetings\n- Attendee profiles\n- Deadlines mentioned outside the calendar\n\nWalk me through:\n- Conflicts – one at a time, explaining what's at stake\n- Meetings I should schedule – follow-ups, pre-meetings, email threads better as calls\n- Gaps – commitments with no time allocated to make progress\n\nProvide two tables only:\n- Full picture (conflicts, prep work, open commitments, required attendees declining)\n- Prioritised actions\n\nThen help me execute.","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.prepareForMeetingLabel":"Prepare for a meeting","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.prepareForMeetingPrompt":"I have a meeting coming up: <entity type='Event'></entity>. Help me prepare.\n\nFirst, gather context:\n- Attendees, agenda, pre-reads, and prior action items\n- My communications with attendees over the last two weeks – open items, what's important to them\n- Related meetings from the recent past – pull transcripts for context\n- Check if I delivered on my prior action items – be direct if I didn't\n\nGive me a one-page briefing:\n- Context: What this meeting is about and why it matters now\n- People: Who's in the room and what they care about\n- Open threads: Anything unresolved that's likely to come up\n- My action items from last time: Did I deliver or not?\n- Talking points: 2–3 things I should proactively raise\n\nIf you flagged any actions for me, help me take them one by one.","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.previousSlideLabel":"Previous","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.reclaimCalendarLabel":"Optimise my calendar","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.reclaimCalendarPrompt":"Help me optimise my time. Analyse my meetings from the past month and the next two months. Exclude non-meetings.\n\nFor each meeting, evaluate:\n- Recurring meeting quality – repeated topics, no decisions, missing action items, updates that could be async\n- Attendee patterns – overlapping groups, consolidation opportunities, meetings I skip/decline, weekly overlap\n- Post-meeting outcomes – review email and Teams activity within 24 hours to infer impact\n\nShow me a summary:\n- Total meetings and hours\n- Recurring vs one-off, organiser vs attendee\n- Key patterns with evidence\n\nThen guide me through an action plan meeting-by-meeting. After approval, create focus time blocks for recovered time.","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.reviewPendingItemsLabel":"Review my pending items","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.reviewPendingItemsPrompt":"Help me clear my backlog. Find everything that's waiting on me right now across:\n- Emails\n- Teams messages\n- Documents (unresolved comments, suggested edits, review requests)\n- Meeting follow-ups\n\nFor each item, show me:\n- What it is and who's asking\n- How long it's been waiting\n- Key context from the thread\n- Recommended action: approve, push back, needs more info, or delegate – and why\n- Link to the source\n\nFlag anything waiting more than 48 hours as overdue.\n\nHelp me take actions with my approval, one by one. Sort by urgency.","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.weeklyCompeteUpdateLabel":"Weekly compete update","scc-deep-work-agent.CardsCarousel.weeklyCompeteUpdatePrompt":"Create a weekly competitive intelligence update for the field team. Here's what I need you to do:\n\n1. External intelligence:\n   * Search the web for the latest moves and announcements from <list 3-5 competitors>. Focus on: product launches, pricing changes, partnerships, executive hires, earnings highlights, and anything that shifts competitive positioning.\n   * Find 3–5 notable industry developments from anywhere in the space – analyst reports, market data, regulatory changes, or emerging trends that the field team should know about.\n   * For every claim, include the source link. No source, no inclusion.\n\n2. Internal intelligence:\n   * Check my email and Teams for any internal threads from the past week discussing competitive developments – field reports, win/loss notes, customer mentions of competitors, or internal strategy discussions.\n   * Pull from any shared documents updated this week that relate to competitive positioning, pricing, or market strategy.\n   * Cross-reference: does our internal conversation match or contradict what's happening externally? Flag any gaps.\n\n3. Structure the update as:\n   * Top competitive moves this week (with source links)\n   * Notable industry developments (with source links)\n   * Internal signal – what our team is seeing and saying\n   * Implications for our positioning – what should the field team know, and what should they say (or stop saying) to customers?\n   * One-line summary at the top: \"This week's biggest competitive development is X because Y.\"\n\n4. Draft an email with the update ready for me to review and send to the field distribution list.\n\nSchedule this to run every Friday at 3pm. After each run, put the draft in my inbox for review before sending.","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkAccessGate.body":"Anthropic models aren't enabled for your tenant. Contact your administrator to enable access.","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkAccessGate.heading":"Access disabled","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkChat.agentName":"Deepwork","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkChat.inputPlaceholder":"Message {0}","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkCoTPreview.previewLabel":"View reasoning","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkCoTPreview.thinkingPlaceholder":"Thinking…","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.balanceDirectsDescription":"See who's getting your attention and who's not.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.balanceDirectsLabel":"Balance time with directs","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.balanceDirectsPrompt":"Analyse my past 6 months of meetings with direct reports.\n\nFor each person, show me:\n- Total meeting time (one-to-ones, shared group meetings, ad-hoc calls)\n- One-to-one consistency (flag gaps >2 weeks)\n- Time balance across directs (who's over/under-indexed)\n- Async communication (email/Teams) to see if low meeting time is offset\n\nBuild an interactive table or dashboard that highlights imbalance at a glance.\n\nRecommend:\n- Who needs more time and where to reduce\n- Flag directs showing stress signals (escalations, missed deadlines, frustration)\n\nOutput only: one data table + 3–5 concise recommendations.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.chiefOfStaffDescription":"Daily briefing: what happened, what's coming, what to do.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.chiefOfStaffLabel":"Be my chief of staff","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.chiefOfStaffPrompt":"Run every morning at 8am. Before my day starts, look at everything that happened since I last checked out and everything coming up today. Here's what I need:\n\n1. Overnight briefing:\n   * Scan emails that came in since 6pm yesterday. Flag anything urgent – escalations, time-sensitive requests, things that will blow up if I don't handle them by noon. For everything else, give me a one-line summary grouped by topic.\n   * Check Teams messages and channels for overnight activity – decisions made without me, questions directed at me, or threads that shifted direction.\n   * Check if any shared documents were updated overnight – especially status trackers, project plans, or anything related to active workstreams. Note what changed and who changed it.\n\n2. Today's game plan:\n   * Pull my calendar for today. For each meeting, tell me: what it's about, who's in the room, and the one thing I need to know going in. For recurring meetings, check the transcript from last time – are there carry-forward action items I owe?\n   * Identify conflicts or double-bookings and suggest which to move.\n   * Flag any meetings where I'm likely to get ambushed – look for recent email or Teams threads with attendees that suggest tension, open issues, or unresolved asks.\n   * Tell me what my top 3 priorities should be today, based on deadlines, urgency signals, and what's been waiting the longest.\n\n3. End-of-day wrap-up (run at 6pm):\n   * Three-line summary: what got done, what didn't, and what carries over to tomorrow.\n\nCite sources for everything – I want to click through to the original email, message, or document. If you see something truly urgent before my morning briefing, ping me on Teams.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.learnNextDescription":"Skill gap analysis from a year of your work patterns.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.learnNextLabel":"What should I learn next","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.learnNextPrompt":"Help me figure out where I should grow. Review my past year of emails, Teams messages, meetings, and documents to identify skill gaps.\n\nAnalyse:\n- Tasks/topics I avoid or delegate - distinguish true gaps from smart delegation\n- Areas of slower response or weaker performance - delayed replies, multiple document revisions, meetings where I ask more than answer\n- Skills peers demonstrate that I don't (e.g., data analysis, exec communication, technical depth)\n- Explicit or implicit feedback signals\n\nFor each skill, give me one bullet with:\n- What to build\n- Why (data-based evidence)\n- What to do this month\n\nList 3 skills. Be direct and honest - no polish.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.planTimeOffDescription":"Find the best week for holiday based on your work data.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.planTimeOffLabel":"Plan my time off","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.planTimeOffPrompt":"I want to take a week off in the next 3 months. Help me choose the best week.\n\nAnalyse my calendar:\n- Meeting load per week\n- Hard commitments (reviews, launches, offsites, deadlines)\n- Last year's calendar for recurring events not yet scheduled\n\nScan email and Teams for signals:\n- Projects ramping up\n- Threads likely to impact that week\n- Directs' planned PTO (avoid overlapping key people)\n\nGive me a concise recommendation:\n- Best week + why\n- Backup option\n- What must be rescheduled or delegated (manageable or not)\n- Any hard blockers (\"don't take this week because X\")\n\nRecommendation only.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.superPowersDescription":"Discover your strengths from 6 months of work patterns.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.superPowersLabel":"What are my super powers","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.superPowersPrompt":"Help me understand what I'm truly best at. Review my last 6 months of emails, Teams messages, meetings, and documents.\n\nAnalyse:\n- Where I spend time – dominant topics, projects, people; what I gravitate toward vs avoid\n- Communication style – concise vs detailed, questions vs answers, leading vs supporting; patterns when at my best vs disengaged\n- Fast loop-closure – which requests I respond to immediately\n- Energy signals – enthusiasm, high-engagement meetings, going beyond scope\n\nOutput only:\n- Top 3 specific superpowers, backed by evidence\n- One honest blind spot\n- A one-line bio reflecting my data-driven working identity\n\nNo preamble or caveats.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.trackDecisionDescription":"Build a sourced decision trail across all channels.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.trackDecisionLabel":"Track a decision end-to-end","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkDigDeeperPrompts.trackDecisionPrompt":"I need to make a decision about <topic>. Before I decide anything, I need to see the full picture of what's already been said, by whom, and where.\n\n1. Build me a decision trail:\n   * Search my emails, Teams messages, meeting transcripts, and shared documents for every discussion related to this topic.\n   * For each entry, log: who said what, when, in which channel (email, Teams, meeting), and what their position or recommendation was.\n   * Identify what options have been on the table – proposals, alternatives, compromises – and who championed each one.\n   * Surface any data or evidence that's been cited to support a position. Cross-check: is the evidence still current? Has anything changed since it was cited?\n   * Map the disagreements: where do people diverge, between whom, and is it about facts, priorities or preferences?\n\n2. Give me a structured decision brief:\n   * The question we're deciding\n   * Options on the table (with who supports each)\n   * Evidence for and against each option (with source links)\n   * Open questions – things we don't have enough information on yet\n   * Your recommendation – based on the weight of evidence, not consensus. If the evidence is split, say so and tell me what additional information would tip it.\n\n3. As new information comes in over the next week – new emails, meetings, or documents related to this topic – update the trail and flag me when something materially changes the picture. When it looks like we have enough signal to decide, tell me.\n\nLink every entry to the source. This needs to be airtight – I'm going to use this to explain the decision to people who weren't in the room.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkExplorePrompts.alignTheTeamDescription":"Map disconnects, draft an action plan, then execute it.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkExplorePrompts.pitchNewProjectDescription":"Research, competitive analysis, and executive deck in one go.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkExplorePrompts.planWeekAheadDescription":"Check commitments, resolve conflicts, and optimise your week.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkExplorePrompts.prepareForMeetingDescription":"Briefing with people profiles, open threads, and action items.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkExplorePrompts.reclaimCalendarDescription":"Analyse 3 months of meetings and act on what's not working.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkExplorePrompts.reviewPendingItemsDescription":"Find everything waiting on you, decide, and clear it.","scc-deep-work-agent.DeepWorkExplorePrompts.weeklyCompeteUpdateDescription":"Web + internal intel combined into a field-ready update.","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkHomePage.agentName":"Deepwork","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkHomePage.bebopInputPlaceholder":"Assign me something","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkHomePage.bebopTitleDark":"What needs to get done?","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkHomePage.bebopTitleLight":" Put me on it.","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkHomePage.inputPlaceholder":"Ask me to build, analyse, research or plan something...","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkHomePage.tasksHeading":"Tasks","scc-deep-work-agent.deepWorkHomePage.title":"Wh