pack.promptPack.promptPackOutputFormatSectionTitle":"Output Format","scc-prompt-pack.promptPack.promptPackSourcesLabel":"Sources","scc-react-acs-vision.sccScreenShareInput.ScreenShareControl.currentSharedSurfaceBrowserTab":"{0} a tab","scc-react-acs-vision.sccScreenShareInput.ScreenShareControl.currentSharedSurfaceScreen":"{0} a screen","scc-react-acs-vision.sccScreenShareInput.ScreenShareControl.currentSharedSurfaceWindow":"{0} a window","scc-react-acs-vision.sccScreenShareInput.ScreenShareControl.sharingLabelPrefix":"Sharing","scc-react-acs-vision.sccScreenShareInput.ScreenShareControl.startScreenShareToolTip":"Start Screen Share","scc-react-acs-vision.sccScreenShareInput.ScreenShareControl.stopScreenShareToolTip":"Stop Screen Share","scc-react-action-agent.watchProgressButton.label":"Watch progress","scc-react-action-agent.watchProgressButton.openTabsLabel":"Open tab","scc-react-agent-auto-invoke-label.researcherAgent.atMentionLabel.askingAgent":"Asking","scc-react-agent-button.agentButton.researcherDescription":"Creates reports based on extensive analysis","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.analyzeDataCardDetailedPrompt":"Analyse the data in [attached file / specified source] and provide a thorough, insight-driven report.\n\nYour analysis should include:\n\n(1) Data overview — what the dataset contains, size, time range, key variables, and any data quality issues (missing values, outliers, inconsistencies),\n(2) Descriptive statistics — key metrics, distributions, averages, medians, and ranges for important variables,\n(3) Trend analysis — how key metrics have changed over time, identifying inflection points and seasonality,\n(4) Correlation and pattern analysis — relationships between variables and notable clusters or segments,\n(5) Anomaly detection — flag any unexpected values, sudden changes, or outliers that warrant investigation,\n(6) Key insights — the 5–7 most important findings stated in plain business language,\n(7) Actionable recommendations — specific, prioritised actions the team should take based on the data,\n(8) Suggested follow-up analyses to go deeper. Include visualisations (tables, charts) where they add clarity.\n\nTone: Clear, analytical, and grounded in evidence.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.analyzeDataCardHover":"Analyse data to provide insights and suggestions","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.analyzeDataCardTitle":"Analyse Data","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.assessFeasibilityCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive feasibility assessment for [proposed initiative / project / investment].\n\nEvaluate viability across all critical dimensions:\n\n(1) Initiative summary — restate the proposal's objectives, scope, expected outcomes, and key assumptions,\n(2) Market feasibility — is there sufficient demand? What evidence supports (or contradicts) the market opportunity? Include TAM estimates and customer validation data,\n(3) Technical feasibility — can we build/deliver this with available technology? Assess architectural complexity, skill requirements, integration challenges, and technology risks,\n(4) Financial feasibility — build a detailed financial model: development/implementation cost, ongoing operating costs, revenue projections (with conservative/base/optimistic scenarios), break-even timeline, ROI, and NPV at appropriate discount rate,\n(5) Operational feasibility — can our organisation execute this? Assess process readiness, capacity constraints, change management requirements, and organisational impact,\n(6) Resource feasibility — do we have (or can we acquire) the people, skills, budget, and infrastructure needed? Identify specific gaps and their solutions,\n(7) Timeline feasibility — is the proposed timeline realistic? Create a high-level schedule with critical path, dependencies, and comparison to similar past initiatives,\n(8) Legal and regulatory feasibility — are there legal barriers, compliance requirements, or IP issues that could block or delay execution?,\n(9) Risk-adjusted assessment — considering all risks identified above, what is the probability-weighted expected outcome?,\n(10) Go/No-Go recommendation — clear verdict with the top 3 reasons supporting your conclusion, conditions under which the recommendation would change,\n(11) If 'Go': the minimum viable version to de-risk with, key milestones, and first 3 actions to take this week.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.assessFeasibilityCardHover":"Determine whether a proposed initiative is viable given constraints","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.assessFeasibilityCardTitle":"Assess Feasibility","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.comparativeAnalysisCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a thorough comparative analysis of [Option A] vs. [Option B] (vs. [Option C] if applicable).\n\nStructure the comparison as:\n\n(1) Overview of each option — what it is, who offers it, and its core value proposition,\n(2) Detailed comparison matrix across these dimensions: pricing/total cost of ownership, features and capabilities, performance and efficiency, scalability, ease of implementation, integration with our existing stack, vendor reliability and support, security and compliance, community and ecosystem, and long-term roadmap/viability,\n(3) For each dimension, provide quantitative data where possible (benchmarks, pricing tiers, SLA numbers),\n(4) Use-case fit analysis — which option is best for which scenarios (e.g., small team vs. enterprise, cost-sensitive vs. performance-first),\n(5) Customer evidence — what do existing users/analysts say about each option (reviews, Gartner/Forrester ratings, case studies),\n(6) Migration and switching considerations — lock-in risks, data portability, and transition costs,\n(7) Recommendation — which option is best for our specific context [describe constraints] and why, with a confidence level,\n(8) A decision-ready summary table a leadership team can review in 2 minutes.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.comparativeAnalysisCardHover":"Compare and contrast between topics across various aspects like price, efficiency, availability etc.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.comparativeAnalysisCardTitle":"Comparative Analysis","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.competitiveAnalysisCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive competitive analysis for [our company/product] in the [industry/market segment].\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Market overview — total addressable market size, growth rate, and key dynamics,\n(2) Competitor identification — the top 5–8 direct and indirect competitors ranked by market share and relevance,\n(3) For each competitor: company overview, product/service offerings, pricing model, target customer segments, key differentiators, recent product launches, funding/revenue (if available), and strategic direction from earnings calls or press releases,\n(4) Feature-by-feature comparison matrix of our product vs. competitors on the dimensions that matter most to buyers,\n(5) SWOT analysis for our position relative to the competitive set,\n(6) Competitive positioning map showing where each player sits on key axes (e.g., price vs. capability, enterprise vs. SMB),\n(7) Emerging threats — startups, adjacent players, or technology shifts that could disrupt the landscape,\n(8) Strategic recommendations — where we should double down, where we're vulnerable, and whitespace opportunities.\n\nTone: Objective, evidence‑based, and non‑promotional.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.competitiveAnalysisCardHover":"Provide a detailed analysis in any industry","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.competitiveAnalysisCardTitle":"Competitive Analysis","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.contentStrategyCardDetailedPrompt":"Develop a comprehensive content marketing strategy for [our company/product] targeting [audience/personas].\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Content audit — analyse our existing content assets (blog posts, whitepapers, videos, webinars, case studies) for performance, gaps, and quality,\n(2) Audience analysis — define 3–4 content personas with their information needs at each stage of the buyer journey (awareness → consideration → decision → retention),\n(3) SEO analysis — identify the top 50 keywords/topics we should target, their search volume, competition difficulty, current ranking position, and content gap analysis vs. competitors,\n(4) Competitor content audit — what are our top 3 competitors publishing, which content performs best for them (backlinks, social shares, search rankings), and where are the content whitespace opportunities?,\n(5) Content pillar strategy — define 4–6 content pillars (core themes) with a hub-and-spoke topic cluster architecture,\n(6) Content format mix — recommended distribution across formats (long-form blog, short-form, video, podcast, infographic, interactive tools, research reports) based on audience preferences and resource efficiency,\n(7) Distribution and amplification plan — channels (organic search, social, email, syndication, paid), posting frequency, and repurposing strategy,\n(8) Editorial calendar — month-by-month content plan for the next 6 months with specific titles, target keywords, formats, personas, funnel stage, and publish dates,\n(9) Production workflow — ideation → brief → draft → review → design → publish → promote process with roles and SLAs,\n(10) Measurement framework — KPIs by content type and funnel stage (traffic, engagement, leads, pipeline influenced, revenue attributed),\n(11) Resource requirements — team, tools (CMS, SEO, analytics, design), and budget needed to execute.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.contentStrategyCardHover":"Develop comprehensive content marketing strategy with SEO analysis and editorial calendar","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.contentStrategyCardTitle":"Content Strategy","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.createAPlanCardDetailedPrompt":"Draft a comprehensive go-to-market plan for launching [product/feature name] targeting [target market/persona].\n\nThe plan should cover:\n\n(1) Executive summary — what we're launching, why now, and the expected business impact,\n(2) Target market definition — ideal customer profile (ICP), buyer personas, and segmentation strategy with TAM/SAM/SOM estimates,\n(3) Value proposition and messaging framework — core positioning, key messages by persona, and competitive differentiation,\n(4) Pricing and packaging strategy — pricing model, tier structure, and competitive pricing comparison,\n(5) Channel strategy — direct sales, partnerships, self-serve, and channel partner approach,\n(6) Marketing plan — awareness, demand generation, content strategy, events, PR, and digital campaigns with indicative budget allocation,\n(7) Sales enablement — training plan, battle cards, demo scripts, and objection handling,\n(8) Launch timeline — phased rollout plan with key milestones (internal readiness, beta, soft launch, GA),\n(9) Success metrics and KPIs — what we'll measure at 30/60/90 days post-launch,\n(10) Risks and contingencies — what could go wrong and how we'll respond.\n\nTone: Strategic, concise, and execution‑oriented.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.createAPlanCardHover":"Draft a comprehensive go-to-market plan for launching a new product","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.createAPlanCardTitle":"Create A Plan","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.createDailyBriefingCardBadge":"Read now","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.createDailyBriefingCardDetailedPrompt":"Create a daily briefing from emails, messages, documents, and meetings to help me prepare for the current workday. Use your understanding of the projects I work on, workstreams I care about, and key people I work with to understand what is relevant and important.\n\nSections:\nA short intro paragraph that provides an overview of my day, i.e. what a personal assistant would tell me to greet me in the morning.\n\nKey updates since yesterday – Include informational updates from the last workday that are likely to impact my work and collaborations.\n\nSuggested tasks for today – Tasks or questions assigned to me that I should handle today. Cross-check that suggested tasks haven't been completed already.\n\nMeeting prep for today – Upcoming meetings only, shown in a table with: Meeting (time, title, organiser), Topic Overview, and Suggested Preparations. Note if inferred or not needed.\n\nRules:\nStart with a header: Daily briefing – Day, Date. Follow with a sub-header stating the timestamp of generation. Start each section with a meaningful emoji. Use only explicitly stated facts; no speculation, interpretations or predictions. If a section has no data, state that.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.createDailyBriefingCardHover":"Show today's updates, tasks, and meetings to help me get started","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.createDailyBriefingCardTitle":"Create A Daily Briefing","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.crisisManagementCardDetailedPrompt":"Develop a comprehensive crisis management plan for [our organisation / specific crisis scenario — e.g., data breach, product failure, PR incident, supply chain disruption].\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Crisis classification framework — define severity levels (Level 1–4) with criteria for escalation and response intensity,\n(2) Scenario planning — for [the specific crisis type or top 5 most likely crisis scenarios]: detailed scenario description, trigger events and warning signs, estimated timeline of how events would unfold,\n(3) Immediate response protocol (first 2 hours) — who is notified, decision authority chain, initial containment actions, and communication blackout rules,\n(4) Crisis team structure — roles and responsibilities (Incident Commander, Communications Lead, Legal Counsel, Technical Lead, Executive Sponsor) with named alternates,\n(5) Communication plan — stakeholder-specific messaging templates for: employees, customers, media/press, investors/board, regulators, and partners. Include holding statements, Q&A documents, and social media response guidelines,\n(6) Operational response — step-by-step technical/operational actions to contain, remediate, and recover,\n(7) Legal and regulatory obligations — mandatory notification requirements, timelines, and documentation,\n(8) Business continuity — how to maintain operations during the crisis, backup plans for critical functions,\n(9) Post-crisis protocol — root cause analysis process, after-action review template, remediation tracking, and organisational learning integration,\n(10) Simulation and training plan — tabletop exercise scenarios, frequency, and participants,\n(11) Resource requirements — tools, retainers (PR firm, outside counsel, forensics firm), and budget provisions needed before a crisis occurs.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.crisisManagementCardHover":"Develop comprehensive crisis response strategies and communication plans","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.crisisManagementCardTitle":"Crisis Management","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.critiqueAnIdeaCardDetailedPrompt":"Critically evaluate the proposal in [attached document / described idea].\n\nProvide a rigorous, balanced critique structured as:\n\n(1) Summary of the proposal — restate the core thesis, key claims, and proposed actions in your own words to confirm understanding,\n(2) Strengths — what the proposal gets right, supported by data or precedent where available,\n(3) Weaknesses and gaps — identify logical flaws, unsupported claims, missing considerations, or overly optimistic assumptions. For each weakness, cite contradictory data, case studies, or expert perspectives,\n(4) Risk analysis — what could go wrong if this proposal is implemented as-is, with likelihood and impact estimates,\n(5) Feasibility assessment — is the timeline realistic? Are the resource requirements accurate? Are there hidden dependencies?,\n(6) Alternative approaches — 2–3 different ways to achieve the same objective that the proposal may not have considered,\n(7) Specific improvement recommendations — line-by-line or section-by-section suggestions to strengthen the proposal,\n(8) Verdict — overall assessment (strong/moderate/weak) with the single most important thing to change before moving forward.\n\nTone: Constructive, rigorous, and respectful.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.critiqueAnIdeaCardHover":"Critique the proposal in a document. Provide supporting data for claims and suggest ways to improve it","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.critiqueAnIdeaCardTitle":"Critique An Idea","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.customerFeedbackCardDetailedPrompt":"Analyse the customer feedback data in [attached file / specified source — e.g., NPS surveys, app store reviews, support tickets, social mentions] and deliver a comprehensive insights report.\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Data summary — total volume analysed, time period, sources, and response demographics,\n(2) Overall sentiment distribution — positive/neutral/negative breakdown with trend over time,\n(3) Theme extraction — identify the top 10–15 recurring themes/topics using frequency and sentiment analysis,\n(4) Top 5 pain points — the most impactful negative themes, ranked by frequency × severity, with representative verbatim quotes,\n(5) Top 5 strengths — what customers consistently praise, with supporting quotes if available,\n(6) Feature requests — the most commonly requested capabilities or improvements, prioritised by volume,\n(7) Competitive mentions — what customers say when comparing us to alternatives,\n(8) Segment analysis — do different customer segments (by size, industry, tenure, plan tier) have different feedback patterns?,\n(9) Trend analysis — which themes are getting better or worse over time, and are there correlations with product releases or events?,\n(10) Root cause hypotheses — for the top pain points, what likely causes them and what teams/processes are involved,\n(11) Prioritised recommendations — a ranked list of the highest-impact improvements we should make, with estimated effort and expected customer impact.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.customerFeedbackCardHover":"Analyse 10,000+ customer reviews to identify top pain points and improvement areas","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.customerFeedbackCardTitle":"Customer Feedback","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.decisionTableCardDetailedPrompt":"Review the transcript and notes from my recent meeting on [topic / meeting name] and create a structured decision table.\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Context — one-paragraph summary of what was being decided and why,\n(2) Decision table with columns: Option Name | Description | Pros | Cons | Cost Estimate | Timeline | Risk Level (H/M/L) | Champion/Advocate | Key Dependencies,\n(3) For each option, capture the arguments made for and against it during the meeting — attribute positions to specific participants where possible,\n(4) Evaluation criteria — list the criteria the group explicitly or implicitly used to evaluate options, weighted by apparent importance,\n(5) Areas of agreement and disagreement — where did participants align, and where were there unresolved tensions?,\n(6) Open questions — issues raised in the meeting that were not resolved,\n(7) Recommended decision — based on the discussion, which option appears to have the strongest support and best fit,\n(8) Next steps — specific action items with owners and deadlines mentioned or implied in the meeting.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.decisionTableCardHover":"Summarise options discussed in meeting into a table with key criteria and next steps","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.decisionTableCardTitle":"Decision Table","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.explainComplexIdeaCardDetailedPrompt":"Take [this complex topic / attached document / technical concept] and translate it into a clear, business-oriented briefing that a non-specialist executive can understand and act on.\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Plain-language summary — explain the core concept in 2–3 paragraphs using analogies and avoiding jargon; if jargon is unavoidable, define each term on first use,\n(2) Why it matters — specifically, why should our business care about this? Connect it to revenue, cost, risk, customer experience, or competitive advantage with concrete examples,\n(3) How it works — a simplified but accurate explanation of the mechanism, process, or technology, with a visual mental model (describe a diagram or flowchart),\n(4) Current state — where does this concept stand today in terms of adoption, maturity, and real-world implementation?,\n(5) Impact on our business — for each major area of our operations (product, sales, marketing, operations, engineering, finance, legal), describe the specific potential impact (positive or negative) and timeframe,\n(6) What our competitors are doing — are peers or competitors already acting on this? Who's leading and who's lagging?,\n(7) Action items — 3–5 specific, prioritised actions we should take in the next 30/60/90 days, with ownership suggestions and decision points,\n(8) Questions to ask — the 5 most important questions leadership should discuss to make informed decisions about this topic,\n(9) Resources for going deeper — 2–3 recommended readings for those who want to understand the details, ranging from a 5-minute overview to a 30-minute deep-dive.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.explainComplexIdeaCardHover":"Translate any complex language or concept into business impact and action items","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.explainComplexIdeaCardTitle":"Explain Complex Idea","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.industryBenchmarksCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive industry benchmarking analysis comparing our key business metrics against [top competitors / industry best-in-class].\n\nAnalyse:\n\n(1) Our current metrics baseline — pull from internal data: CAC, churn rate (monthly/annual), LTV, LTV:CAC ratio, payback period, net revenue retention, gross margin, operating margin, revenue per employee, and customer satisfaction scores,\n(2) Industry benchmarks — for each metric, provide the industry median, top quartile, and top decile values for companies at our stage and in our segment, sourced from OpenView, KeyBanc, Bessemer, SaaS Capital, and public company filings,\n(3) Competitive estimates — for our top 5 competitors, estimate these metrics based on available data (public filings, analyst reports, job posting volume as a proxy for growth, pricing pages, customer count disclosures),\n(4) Gap analysis — where we are above, at, or below benchmarks, with the magnitude of each gap,\n(5) Decomposition — for metrics where we underperform, break them down into component drivers (e.g., CAC = Marketing Spend / New Customers → is it a spend efficiency or conversion problem?),\n(6) Trend analysis — how our metrics have trended over the past 4–8 quarters vs. how benchmarks have moved,\n(7) Cohort analysis — do our metrics vary significantly by customer segment, geography, or acquisition channel?,\n(8) Improvement modelling — if we close the gap to top-quartile performance on our weakest 3 metrics, what's the projected financial impact?,\n(9) Recommendations — specific, prioritised initiatives to improve our weakest metrics, with estimated effort and expected improvement.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.industryBenchmarksCardHover":"Compare our customer acquisition costs, churn rates, and LTV against top competitors","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.industryBenchmarksCardTitle":"Industry Benchmarks","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.investigateIncidentCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a thorough investigation and analysis of [the incident — e.g., service outage, security breach, customer escalation, compliance violation, product defect].\n\nProvide:\n\n(1) Incident summary — what happened, when, duration, scope of impact (users/systems/revenue affected), and current status,\n(2) Timeline reconstruction — minute-by-minute (or hour-by-hour) chronology of events from first signal to resolution, based on available logs, communications, and reports,\n(3) Root cause analysis — use the 5-Whys methodology and an Ishikawa (fishbone) diagram to identify the root cause(s), distinguishing between the triggering event and underlying systemic factors,\n(4) Contributing factors — organisational, process, technology, and human factors that allowed this to happen (e.g., missing monitoring, unclear ownership, technical debt, training gaps),\n(5) Precedent research — have similar incidents occurred in our organisation before? Summarise patterns. Also research how other companies have handled analogous incidents and what they learned,\n(6) Impact assessment — quantify the full impact: customer impact (SLA breaches, churn risk), financial impact (revenue lost, remediation cost, potential penalties), reputational impact, and employee/team impact,\n(7) Immediate response evaluation — what we did well and what we could have done differently in our initial response,\n(8) Remediation recommendations — short-term fixes (immediate/this week), medium-term improvements (this quarter), and long-term systemic changes (this year), each with owner, effort estimate, and priority,\n(9) Prevention plan — specific controls, monitoring, processes, or architectural changes to prevent recurrence,\n(10) Communication strategy — recommended messaging for affected stakeholders (customers, leadership, regulators) acknowledging the issue and committing to improvements.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.investigateIncidentCardHover":"Research root causes, precedents, and recommend responses for an issue","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.investigateIncidentCardTitle":"Investigate Incident","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.investmentResearchCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct thorough investment research on [emerging companies in X sector / specific company name] for [investment stage — e.g., Series A consideration].\n\nProvide:\n\n(1) Market thesis — why this sector is attractive for investment right now, supported by market size data, growth projections, and tailwind analysis,\n(2) Company identification — if sector-level: identify the top 8–10 most promising companies; if company-specific: proceed to deep-dive,\n(3) For each company: founding team and leadership assessment (backgrounds, track record, domain expertise), product/technology overview and differentiation, stage of development and key milestones achieved,\n(4) Business model analysis — revenue model, unit economics (if available), customer acquisition strategy, and path to profitability,\n(5) Competitive positioning — how they compare to both incumbents and other startups in the space,\n(6) Financial overview — funding history, burn rate, runway, valuation trajectory, and cap table considerations,\n(7) IP and technology moat — patents, proprietary data, regulatory approvals, switching costs, or network effects,\n(8) Risk factors — scientific/technical risk, regulatory risk, market timing risk, team risk, and competitive risk,\n(9) Comparable transactions — recent deals, valuations, and exits in the sector that set pricing benchmarks,\n(10) Due diligence red flags — anything that warrants deeper investigation,\n(11) Investment recommendation — invest/pass/watch with target valuation range and key conditions.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.investmentResearchCardHover":"Research and analyse emerging companies for potential Series A investment","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.investmentResearchCardTitle":"Investment Research","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.mADueDiligenceCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct comprehensive due diligence on [target company] as a potential acquisition for [our company].\n\nStructure the analysis across:\n\n(1) Strategic rationale — why this acquisition makes sense (market expansion, technology acqui-hire, customer base, competitive positioning), synergy thesis, and alignment with our strategy,\n(2) Company overview — history, founding team, leadership, organisational structure, culture, headcount trends, and Glassdoor/employee sentiment,\n(3) Financial analysis — revenue trajectory (3-year), growth rate, gross and operating margins, burn rate, cash position, debt obligations, revenue quality (recurring vs. one-time, concentration risk), and working capital dynamics,\n(4) Customer analysis — customer count, logos, segment mix, retention rates, NRR, top-10 customer revenue concentration, and contract terms,\n(5) Product and technology — product architecture, tech stack, code quality indicators, technical debt, IP portfolio (patents, trade secrets), and integration complexity with our stack,\n(6) Market position — market share, competitive differentiation, analyst coverage, and brand strength,\n(7) Legal and compliance — pending litigation, regulatory compliance status, data privacy practices, material contracts, and any restrictive agreements,\n(8) HR and talent — key person dependencies, employment contracts, retention risk for critical employees, compensation structure, and pending equity vesting,\n(9) Synergy modelling — revenue synergies (cross-sell, upsell, market expansion) and cost synergies (headcount, infrastructure, vendor consolidation) with confidence-weighted estimates,\n(10) Valuation — DCF, comparable transactions, public comps, and recommended offer range with key assumptions,\n(11) Integration considerations — integration complexity, day-1 requirements, 100-day plan outline, and cultural risk factors,\n(12) Red flags and deal-breakers — issues discovered that could reduce value or warrant walking away.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.mADueDiligenceCardHover":"Conduct comprehensive due diligence on potential acquisition target including financial analysis","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.mADueDiligenceCardTitle":"M&A Due Diligence","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.marketTrendsAnalysisCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive market trends analysis for the [industry/sector].\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Current market overview — size, growth rate, and stage of maturity,\n(2) Top 5–7 macro trends reshaping the industry right now with evidence (data points, examples, analyst quotes),\n(3) Emerging micro-trends that are early-stage but have high potential impact within 12–24 months,\n(4) Technology shifts — which technologies are gaining adoption, which are declining, and what's creating new categories,\n(5) Customer behaviour changes — how buyer expectations, purchasing patterns, and preferences are evolving,\n(6) Regulatory and policy trends — upcoming legislation, standards, or government actions that will affect the market,\n(7) Investment signals — where VC/PE money is flowing, recent M&A activity, and what it signals about market direction,\n(8) Geographic dynamics — which regions are growing fastest and why,\n(9) Impact assessment — for each major trend, rate the potential impact on our business (high/medium/low) and the urgency to act,\n(10) Strategic implications — what should we start, stop, or accelerate based on these trends?","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.marketTrendsAnalysisCardHover":"Identify emerging trends and market dynamics in any industry","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.marketTrendsAnalysisCardTitle":"Market Trends Analysis","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.multiModelComparativeAnalysisCardBadge":"Multi-model","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.multiModelComparativeAnalysisCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a thorough comparative analysis of [Option A] vs. [Option B] (vs. [Option C] if applicable).\n\nStructure the comparison as:\n(1) Overview of each option — what it is, who offers it, and its core value proposition,\n(2) Detailed comparison matrix across these dimensions: pricing/total cost of ownership, features and capabilities, performance and efficiency, scalability, ease of implementation, integration with our existing stack, reliability and support, security and compliance, community and ecosystem, and long-term roadmap/viability,\n(3) For each dimension, provide quantitative data where possible (benchmarks, pricing tiers, SLA numbers),\n(4) Use-case fit analysis — which option is best for which scenarios (e.g., small team vs. enterprise, cost-sensitive vs. performance-first),\n(5) Customer evidence — what do existing users/analysts say about each option (reviews, Gartner/Forrester ratings, case studies),\n(6) Migration and switching considerations — lock-in risks, data portability, and transition costs,\n(7) Recommendation — which option is best for our specific context [describe constraints] and why, with a confidence level, and\n(8) A decision-ready summary table a leadership team can review in 2 minutes.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.multiModelComparativeAnalysisCardHover":"Compare and contrast between topics across various aspects like price, efficiency, availability etc.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.multiModelComparativeAnalysisCardTitle":"Comparative Analysis","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.optimizeProcessCardDetailedPrompt":"Analyse and optimise [the specified workflow / business process — e.g., customer onboarding, quarterly planning, incident response, procurement approval].\n\nProvide:\n\n(1) Current state mapping — document the existing process end-to-end: steps, decision points, handoffs, systems used, roles involved, and typical timeline. Pull from any available process documentation, and interviews or descriptions I provide,\n(2) Pain point identification — where does the process break down? Identify bottlenecks (steps with longest wait times), failure points (where errors or rework occur most), unnecessary steps (that add time but not value), manual work that could be automated, and unclear ownership or handoff friction,\n(3) Performance baseline — current metrics: cycle time (end-to-end and per-step), throughput, error/rework rate, cost per transaction, and customer/internal satisfaction,\n(4) Best practice research — how do best-in-class organisations run this process? Reference frameworks, methodologies (Lean, Six Sigma, BPR), and specific case studies from similar companies,\n(5) Industry benchmarks — what are the target metrics that top-performing organisations achieve for this process?,\n(6) Optimisation opportunities — for each identified pain point, propose a specific improvement with: description, expected impact (time saved, error reduction, cost decrease), implementation complexity (low/medium/high), and dependencies,\n(7) Automation assessment — which steps are candidates for automation (RPA, workflow automation, AI/ML)? Estimate the automation potential and ROI,\n(8) Recommended future state — redesigned process flow with changes highlighted, including new tools/systems needed, revised roles, and updated SLAs,\n(9) Implementation roadmap — phased plan: quick wins (Week 1–4), process redesign (Month 2–3), automation implementation (Month 3–6), with change management considerations,\n(10) Measurement plan — KPIs to track improvement, baseline → target values, and review cadence.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.optimizeProcessCardHover":"Research best practices and benchmarks to improve an existing workflow","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.optimizeProcessCardTitle":"Optimise Process","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.partnershipOpportunitiesCardDetailedPrompt":"Identify and evaluate strategic partnership opportunities with [enterprise software vendors / companies in X sector] for [our company/product].\n\nProvide:\n\n(1) Partnership strategy framework — what types of partnerships we should pursue (technology integration, co-sell, reseller, OEM, joint development) and why, aligned with our strategic goals,\n(2) Market scan — identify 10–15 potential partner companies with brief profiles (size, products, customer base, market position, partnership philosophy),\n(3) Shortlist evaluation — for the top 5–7 candidates, deep-dive on: strategic fit (do our value propositions complement each other?), customer overlap and combined TAM expansion, technical integration feasibility and architecture compatibility, cultural and organisational fit, financial model (revenue share, referral fees, joint investment),\n(4) Competitive dynamics — which partners also work with our competitors, and what exclusivity considerations should we have?,\n(5) Partnership precedents — case studies of successful partnerships in our space, including how they were structured and what made them work,\n(6) Risk assessment — for each shortlisted partner: dependency risk, IP exposure, brand risk, and channel conflict concerns,\n(7) Approach strategy — for each target, the optimal entry point (executive sponsor, partner program, mutual customer introduction), initial value proposition, and conversation framework,\n(8) Deal structure templates — recommended commercial terms and partnership tier structures,\n(9) Success metrics — how to measure partnership health and ROI at 6 and 12 months.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.partnershipOpportunitiesCardHover":"Identify and evaluate potential strategic partnerships with enterprise software vendors","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.partnershipOpportunitiesCardTitle":"Partnership Opportunities","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.prepareForAMeetingCardDetailedPrompt":"Prepare a comprehensive meeting brief for my upcoming meeting with [person/company/team] on [date/topic].\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Meeting context — what this meeting is about and why it was scheduled, pulling from my calendar invite and any related email threads,\n(2) Attendee profiles — who is attending, their roles, recent activity, and any prior interactions I've had with them (from emails, Teams, past meeting notes),\n(3) Background on the topic — key facts, data points, and recent developments I should be aware of,\n(4) Summary of any related documents or presentations that have been shared,\n(5) 5–7 talking points I should raise,\n(6) Potential questions they may ask and suggested responses,\n(7) Open action items from any previous meetings with these stakeholders,\n(8) Recommended outcomes and next steps to push for. Format as a scannable one-pager I can review 10 minutes before the meeting.\n\nTone: Confident, customer‑centric, and pragmatic.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.prepareForAMeetingCardHover":"Prepare for an upcoming meeting","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.prepareForAMeetingCardTitle":"Prepare for a Meeting","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.productLaunchAnalysisCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a thorough product launch readiness analysis for [product name] planned for [Q4 / specific date].\n\nEvaluate:\n\n(1) Market readiness — is the target market ready for this product? Analyse demand signals, search trends, customer requests in our pipeline, and early interest from beta/preview users,\n(2) Competitive timing — what are competitors launching or announcing in the same timeframe? Is our window of differentiation still open?,\n(3) Product readiness — based on available roadmap documents and feature lists, assess completeness against must-have vs. nice-to-have features for launch,\n(4) Target audience validation — does our ICP and messaging resonate based on early feedback, survey data, and win/loss analysis?,\n(5) Pricing validation — how does our planned pricing compare to alternatives and willingness-to-pay data?,\n(6) Channel readiness — are sales teams trained? Are partner channels activated? Is self-serve onboarding built and tested?,\n(7) Marketing readiness — content pipeline (blog posts, case studies, demos, landing pages), launch event planning, PR/analyst briefings, and demand gen campaigns status,\n(8) Operational readiness — support team staffing and training, documentation, SLA commitments, and infrastructure capacity,\n(9) Risk register — top 10 launch risks with mitigations and owners,\n(10) Launch checklist — a comprehensive go/no-go checklist organised by function (Product, Engineering, Marketing, Sales, Support, Legal),\n(11) Post-launch measurement plan — KPIs to track at day 1, week 1, month 1, and quarter 1 with target benchmarks.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.productLaunchAnalysisCardHover":"Assess market readiness and competitive landscape for product launching in Q4","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.productLaunchAnalysisCardTitle":"Product Launch Analysis","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.projectStatusReportCardDetailedPrompt":"Create an executive-ready project status report for [Project Name]. Pull from recent emails, Teams messages, meeting transcripts, and shared documents related to this project.\n\nThe report should include:\n\n(1) An executive summary of overall project health (on track / at risk / off track),\n(2) Progress against key milestones and deliverables with percentage completion,\n(3) Work completed this period vs. planned,\n(4) Top 3–5 risks and issues with severity ratings and proposed mitigations,\n(5) Budget status — spend to date vs. forecast,\n(6) Resource utilisation and any staffing concerns,\n(7) Key decisions needed from leadership,\n(8) Upcoming milestones for the next 2 weeks,\n(9) A RAG (Red/Amber/Green) status table for each workstream. Use a professional tone suitable for C-suite distribution.\n\nAdditional Instructions: Prioritise clarity, technical rigor, and brevity.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.projectStatusReportCardHover":"Create an executive status report on any project","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.projectStatusReportCardTitle":"Project Status Report","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.regulatoryComplianceCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive regulatory compliance analysis for [our SaaS platform / product / operation] regarding [GDPR, CCPA, and any other relevant data privacy regulations] as we plan to [expand into X market / launch Y feature / process Z type of data].\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Regulatory landscape overview — which regulations apply to us based on our customer locations, data processing activities, and corporate structure,\n(2) Requirements mapping — for each applicable regulation, list every relevant requirement organised by category (data collection, consent, storage, processing, transfer, breach notification, data subject rights, DPO appointment, records of processing),\n(3) Gap analysis — compare each requirement against our current policies, technical controls, and operational practices, rating each as: compliant / partially compliant / non-compliant / unknown,\n(4) Risk exposure — for each gap, quantify the potential penalty (financial and reputational), enforcement likelihood based on recent regulatory actions, and business impact if we don't remediate,\n(5) Cross-regulation conflicts — identify areas where different regulations impose conflicting or additive requirements,\n(6) Technical requirements — specific technical controls we need (encryption standards, data residency, anonymisation, consent management, audit trail, deletion capabilities),\n(7) Remediation roadmap — prioritised list of actions to achieve compliance, with estimated effort, cost, responsible teams, and target dates,\n(8) Vendor and third-party implications — what compliance obligations flow to our sub-processors and how to manage them,\n(9) Ongoing compliance program — processes for monitoring regulatory changes, periodic assessments, and employee training,\n(10) Document templates — outline the key policies and documentation we need to create or update (privacy policy, DPIA template, data processing agreements, breach response plan).","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.regulatoryComplianceCardHover":"Analyse GDPR and CCPA compliance requirements for our SaaS platform expansion","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.regulatoryComplianceCardTitle":"Regulatory Compliance","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.researchATopicCardDetailedPrompt":"Create a comprehensive, well-structured research report on the current state and future trajectory of [topic].\n\nThe report should include:\n\n(1) An executive summary with key takeaways,\n(2) Historical context and how the topic has evolved over the past 5 years,\n(3) Current landscape — major players, technologies, methodologies, and market dynamics,\n(4) Key trends and emerging developments supported by data,\n(5) Challenges, open questions, and areas of active debate,\n(6) Expert and analyst perspectives from credible sources,\n(7) Implications for enterprise decision-makers,\n(8) A forward-looking outlook for the next 2–3 years. Use data from my organisation's files, emails, and meetings where relevant, and supplement with authoritative external sources. Format with clear headings, bullet points for key findings, and inline citations.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.researchATopicCardHover":"Create a detailed report on any topic","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.researchATopicCardTitle":"Research A Topic","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.riskAssessmentCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive risk assessment for [expanding operations into X market / launching Y initiative / undertaking Z project].\n\nStructure the analysis as:\n\n(1) Scope definition — what exactly is being evaluated and what assumptions underpin the plan,\n(2) Risk identification — catalogue all material risks across categories: market/demand, competitive, regulatory/legal, operational, financial, technology, talent/HR, geopolitical, reputational, and supply chain,\n(3) For each risk: description, root causes, likelihood (1–5), impact (1–5), risk score (L×I), velocity (how fast it could materialise), and leading indicators to monitor,\n(4) Risk heat map — visual prioritisation of all risks plotted by likelihood vs. impact,\n(5) Top 10 risks deep-dive — for the highest-scoring risks, provide detailed scenario analysis (best/base/worst case), historical precedents or case studies where this risk materialised for similar organisations,\n(6) Mitigation strategies — specific, actionable mitigations for each top risk with estimated cost and effectiveness,\n(7) Risk interdependencies — which risks are correlated and could trigger cascade effects,\n(8) Residual risk after mitigations — what's the remaining exposure if we implement the recommended controls,\n(9) Risk governance recommendations — who should own each risk, monitoring cadence, and escalation thresholds.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.riskAssessmentCardHover":"Evaluate potential risks for expanding operations","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.riskAssessmentCardTitle":"Risk Assessment","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.strategicPlanningCardDetailedPrompt":"Develop a comprehensive 5-year strategic plan for [our company / division / product line].\n\nThe plan should include:\n\n(1) Situation analysis — where we are today: revenue, market share, customer base, product portfolio, organisational capabilities, and financial position, pulling from internal documents and data,\n(2) External environment analysis — market trends, competitive landscape, regulatory outlook, technology disruption, and macroeconomic factors using PESTLE framework,\n(3) Internal assessment — core competencies, resource gaps, cultural strengths/weaknesses, and organisational readiness using VRIO framework,\n(4) Vision and strategic intent — where we want to be in 5 years in measurable terms (revenue, market position, customer metrics, geographic presence),\n(5) Strategic pillars — 3–5 major strategic themes that will drive the vision, with clear rationale for each,\n(6) Growth initiatives — for each pillar, 2–4 specific initiatives with descriptions, expected impact, investment required, and timeline,\n(7) Financial projections — revenue, cost, and profitability model for each year, with assumptions clearly stated,\n(8) Resource requirements — talent, technology, capital, and partnerships needed to execute,\n(9) Risk scenarios — model 3 scenarios (optimistic/base/pessimistic) with key assumptions and trigger points for strategy adjustment,\n(10) Implementation roadmap — phased execution plan with yearly milestones, OKRs, and governance structure,\n(11) Quick wins — 3–5 initiatives that can generate momentum in the first 6 months,\n(12) Decision points — key decisions that need to be made in Year 1 to set the right trajectory.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.strategicPlanningCardHover":"Develop a comprehensive 5-year strategic plan with market analysis and growth initiatives","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.strategicPlanningCardTitle":"Strategic Planning","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.summarizeResearchCardDetailedPrompt":"Analyse and synthesise the key findings from the [attached papers / research on topic].\n\nFor each source:\n\n(1) Citation — full reference (author, title, publication, year),\n(2) Research question and methodology — what they studied and how,\n(3) Key findings — the 3–5 most important results stated in plain language,\n(4) Data quality — sample size, statistical significance, and any limitations the authors acknowledge. Then provide a cross-paper synthesis:\n(5) Consensus findings — what do most studies agree on?,\n(6) Contradictions and debates — where do findings conflict, and what might explain the differences?,\n(7) Research gaps — what hasn't been studied yet that would be valuable to know?,\n(8) Practical implications — what do these findings mean for our business decisions, translated from academic language into actionable insights,\n(9) Confidence assessment — how strong is the overall evidence base (robust / moderate / preliminary),\n(10) Recommended reading — if I can only read a couple of these papers, which ones and why?","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.summarizeResearchCardHover":"Extract key findings from multiple academic papers on any topic","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.summarizeResearchCardTitle":"Summarise Research","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.sustainabilityAssessmentCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive sustainability assessment for [our organisation].\n\nInclude:\n\n(1) Carbon footprint baseline — estimate our Scope 1 (direct emissions), Scope 2 (energy), and Scope 3 (supply chain, travel, commuting, product use) emissions using available data on our operations, facilities, workforce, and supply chain,\n(2) Benchmarking — how does our carbon intensity compare to industry peers and best-in-class companies of similar size and sector?,\n(3) Materiality assessment — identify the ESG issues most material to our business across environmental, social, and governance dimensions, mapped to stakeholder priorities (investors, customers, employees, regulators),\n(4) Regulatory landscape — current and upcoming sustainability reporting requirements (CSRD, SEC climate disclosure, TCFD, ISSB) and our readiness for each,\n(5) Reduction opportunities — identify and quantify the top 15–20 emission reduction initiatives across energy, travel, procurement, operations, and product design, with estimated cost, CO₂ reduction, and implementation timeline,\n(6) Financial analysis — for each initiative, model the business case: upfront investment, annual savings, payback period, and co-benefits (employee satisfaction, brand value, regulatory risk reduction),\n(7) Science-based targets — recommend emission reduction targets aligned with SBTi methodology and Paris Agreement goals,\n(8) Sustainability roadmap — phased 5-year plan with near-term quick wins (Year 1), medium-term structural changes (Years 2–3), and long-term transformational efforts (Years 4–5),\n(9) Stakeholder communication — framework for reporting progress to investors, customers, and employees,\n(10) Governance structure — recommended roles, metrics, review cadence, and accountability mechanisms to drive execution.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.sustainabilityAssessmentCardHover":"Evaluate our carbon footprint, identify reduction opportunities, and develop sustainability roadmap","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.sustainabilityAssessmentCardTitle":"Sustainability Assessment","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.technologyEvaluationCardDetailedPrompt":"Conduct a comprehensive technology evaluation comparing [Technology A, B, C] for [use case — e.g., enterprise data warehouse migration].\n\nStructure the evaluation as:\n\n(1) Requirements baseline — what our specific needs are (data volume, query patterns, user count, latency requirements, compliance needs, existing stack),\n(2) Architecture comparison — how each solution is designed, key architectural trade-offs, and fit with our current infrastructure,\n(3) Feature comparison matrix — detailed side-by-side on: data ingestion, query performance, concurrency handling, storage formats, ML/AI integration, real-time capabilities, security & encryption, IAM, audit logging, and data governance,\n(4) Performance benchmarks — TPC-DS or equivalent benchmark results, real-world performance comparisons from third-party evaluations,\n(5) Total Cost of Ownership — 3-year TCO model including compute, storage, data transfer, licensing, training, migration, and ongoing operations for our projected workload,\n(6) Migration complexity — effort to migrate from our current platform, tooling support, data transfer mechanisms, and estimated timeline,\n(7) Vendor ecosystem — partner integrations, marketplace, third-party tooling support, and community size,\n(8) Vendor viability — financial health, product roadmap direction, analyst ratings (Gartner, Forrester), and customer references in our industry,\n(9) Risk assessment — lock-in risk, data portability, contractual gotchas, and exit strategy for each option,\n(10) Weighted scoring model — score each option against our prioritised criteria and provide a final recommendation with confidence level.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.technologyEvaluationCardHover":"Compare cloud providers (AWS, Azure, GCP) for enterprise data warehouse migration","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.explorePromptCard.technologyEvaluationCardTitle":"Technology Evaluation","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.historyTab.noSearchResultsDescription":"Try a different search term","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.historyTab.noSearchResultsTitle":"No results found","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.historyTab.searchHistoryListLabel":"Search history list","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.historyTab.searchHistoryPlaceholder":"Search history...","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.historyTab.untitledConversation":"Untitled conversation","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.savedTab.noSavedItemsTitle":"There's no saved items yet","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.savedTab.noSavedPromptsDescription":"All the prompts you save in Researcher will be stored here for quick reference.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.savedTab.noSavedPromptsTitle":"You haven't saved a researcher prompt yet","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.savedTab.savedPromptsErrorDescription":"Please try again.","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.savedTab.savedPromptsErrorTitle":"Something went wrong","scc-react-agent-homepage-components.researcher.savedTab.savedPromptsLabel":"Saved p